author: Elizabeth Roche
title: India requests Philippines’ support for its membership of APEC
text:
New Delhi: India has requested the Philippines to support its candidature for membership of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation or APEC. India’s request was made by foreign minister Sushma Swaraj at meeting with her Philippines counterpart Alfred Del Rosario in New Delhi on Wednesday.
In its response, the Philippines has assured India of support, an Indian official said on Thursday.
APEC is a forum of 21 Pacific Rim countries and promotes free trade throughout the Asia-Pacific region. The Philippines currently holds the rotating presidency of the grouping.
